[CENTER][B][SIZE=6]WorldGuard ExtraFlags Plus[/SIZE][/B][/CENTER]

[B]Release 4.3.13[/B]

An advanced WorldGuard extension that adds over 30+ extra region flags for full control of player behavior, teleportation, and region rules — featuring Folia support, item blocking (Mace, Firework, Wind Charge, Totem, vanilla Spears), throwable-only blocking (disable-throw for egg, snowball, pearl, XP bottle), optional PacketEvents/ProtocolLib packet hooks for full disable-completely coverage, and fully customizable messages.

[CENTER]🧱 [B]Folia Ready[/B] | ⚙️ [B]Custom Messages[/B] | 🪓 [B]Disable Mace, Totem, Trident, Spears & More[/B] | 🥚 [B]Disable-throw (egg / snowball / pearl / XP bottle)[/B][/CENTER]
[CENTER]🎚️ [B]XP-Based or PlaceholderAPI (integer output) based region entry limits[/B][/CENTER]

[SIZE=4][COLOR=#E9d502][B]⚠️ WARNING DO NOT USE BOTH PLUGINS TOGETHER![/B][/COLOR][/SIZE]

If you're upgrading from [I]WorldGuardExtraFlags[/I] to [I]WorldGuardExtraFlagsPlus[/I], make sure to:
[LIST]
[*][B]Remove[/B] the old [I]WorldGuardExtraFlags.jar[/I] plugin file
[*][B]Only keep[/B] [I]WorldGuardExtraFlagsPlus.jar[/I] on your server
[*]Both plugins cannot coexist - they will conflict with each other
[/LIST]

[B][SIZE=5]Key Features[/SIZE][/B]
[LIST]
[*]✅ [B]Folia support[/B] – fully compatible with async region handling
[*]🛡️ [B]New flag:[/B] [I]disable-completely[/I] – blocks all usage of specified items (MACE, FIREWORK_ROCKET, WIND_CHARGE, TOTEM_OF_UNDYING, TRIDENT, vanilla spear tiers 1.21.11+, plus [B]SPEAR[/B] for all tiers at once)
  [*][I]Note: permit-completely is replaced. Please use disable-completely instead.[/I]
  [*][I]Spear Lunge (packet STAB, including Lunge enchant) requires PacketEvents or ProtocolLib on the server for reliable blocking; without either, Lunge may bypass region checks.[/I]
[*]🎯 [B]New flag:[/B] [I]disable-throw[/I] – blocks launching only these throwables: [B]EGG[/B], [B]SNOWBALL[/B], [B]ENDER_PEARL[/B], [B]EXPERIENCE_BOTTLE[/B]. Tridents and wind charges stay on [I]disable-completely[/I].
[*]🎚️ [B]New flags:[/B] [I]entry-min-level[/I] / [I]entry-max-level[/I] – restrict entry by [B]XP level[/B] or [B]PlaceholderAPI values[/B]
[*]💬 [B]Customizable messages[/B] via [I]messages-wgefp.yml[/I] (disable, recolor, or use placeholders)
[*]🔁 [B]Message cooldown system[/B] – prevents spam (default: 3 seconds)
[*]🏪 [B]New flag:[/B] [I]villager-trade[/I] – control villager trading in regions
[*]🚫 [B]New flag:[/B] [I]disable-collision[/I] – disable player collision in regions
  [*][I]Uses Minecraft's native scoreboard teams to control collision. TAB plugin is supported with API integration. May conflict with other plugins that use teams. See (public-documents/disable-collision flag documentation.md) for details.[/I]
[*]📝 [B]PlaceholderAPI Chat Integration[/B] – chat prefix/suffix supports PlaceholderAPI placeholders
[*]🧱 [B]New flags:[/B] [I]allow-block-place[/I] / [I]deny-block-place[/I] / [I]allow-block-break[/I] / [I]deny-block-break[/I] – fine-grained block placement and breaking control
[*]📦 [B]New flags:[/B] [I]deny-item-drops[/I] / [I]deny-item-pickup[/I] – restrict specific items from being dropped or picked up (works when WorldGuard allows drops/pickups)
[*]🔨 [B]New flag:[/B] [I]permit-workbenches[/I] – block workbench usage (anvil, crafting table, ender chest, etc.) and crafting table crafting in regions
  [*][I]Note: permit-workbenches CRAFT now only blocks crafting table (3x3) crafting, not inventory (2x2) crafting. Use inventory-craft flag to block inventory crafting.[/I]
[*]🎨 [B]New flag:[/B] [I]inventory-craft[/I] – block inventory crafting (2x2 grid) in regions
[*]🛡️ [B]Godmode & Fly Flag Enhancement[/B] – The [I]godmode[/I] and [I]fly[/I] flags now also disable EssentialsX godmode/fly when entering regions with these flags disabled (EssentialsX integration)
[*]👥 [B]New flag:[/B] [I]player-count-limit[/I] – limit maximum number of players in a region
[*]🎯 [B]New flag (experimental):[/B] [I]chambered-enderpearl[/I] – mitigates chambered ender pearl bypasses (pearls thrown outside denied regions are removed when the shooter enters a region where the flag denies); subject to change.
[/LIST]


[B][SIZE=5]About[/SIZE][/B]
WorldGuard protects land by defining regions.  
[B]WorldGuard ExtraFlags Plus[/B] extends it with even more customization — adding powerful flags that modify gameplay, teleportation, commands, and behavior within regions.



[B][SIZE=5]Included Flags (30+)[/SIZE][/B]
Here's a quick overview — all managed with standard WorldGuard flag commands.

[CODE]
[teleport-on-entry / teleport-on-exit]  [command-on-entry / command-on-exit]
[console-command-on-entry / console-command-on-exit]  [walk-speed / fly-speed]
[keep-inventory / keep-exp]  [chat-prefix / chat-suffix]  [godmode]
[blocked-effects]  [respawn-location]  [worldedit]  [give-effects]
[fly]  [play-sounds]  [frostwalker]  [nether-portals]  [glide](elytra-blocker)
[chunk-unload]  [item-durability]  [join-location](not-on-folia)
[/CODE]

[B]New in Plus:[/B]

[CODE]
[disable-completely]  [disable-throw]
[entry-min-level / entry-max-level]
[villager-trade]  [disable-collision]  [deny-item-drops / deny-item-pickup]
[allow-block-place / deny-block-place]  [allow-block-break / deny-block-break]
[permit-workbenches]  [inventory-craft]  [player-count-limit]
[chambered-enderpearl](experimental)
[/CODE]



[B][SIZE=5]📖 Flag Usage Guide[/SIZE][/B]

For comprehensive usage examples and detailed flag documentation, see:
[URL=https://github.com/tins-dev/WorldGuardExtraFlagsPlus/blob/master/.media/flag-usages.md]Complete Flag Usage Guide[/URL]


[B][SIZE=5]Version Compatibility[/SIZE][/B]
[TABLE]
[TR][TH]Minecraft[/TH][TH]WorldGuard[/TH][TH]ExtraFlagsPlus[/TH][TH]Support[/TH][/TR]
[TR][TD]1.20 – 1.21.11[/TD][TD]7.0.15+[/TD][TD]4.3.13+[/TD][TD][COLOR=#00FF00]✅ Active[/COLOR][/TD][/TR]
[TR][TD]1.7 – 1.19[/TD][TD]Older[/TD][TD]-[/TD][TD][COLOR=#FF0000]❌ No support[/COLOR][/TD][/TR]
[/TABLE]

The jar declares [I]api-version: 1.21[/I] in [I]plugin.yml[/I] so Paper [B]1.21.x[/B] servers (and forks such as Canvas) load it; the project still compiles against the pinned Paper API artifact in the root [I]pom.xml[/I].



[B][SIZE=5]Message Customization[/SIZE][/B]
All plugin messages live in [I]plugins/WorldGuard/messages-wgefp.yml[/I].

[LIST]
[*]Edit freely to match your style
[*]Use placeholders: [I]{required}[/I], [I]{current}[/I], [I]{item}[/I], [I]{workbench}[/I] (e.g. [I]disable-throw-blocked[/I] uses [I]{item}[/I])
[*]Supports color codes: [I]&c[/I], [I]&7[/I], etc.
[*]Disable messages with [I]""[/I]
[*]Reload instantly using [I]/wgefp reload[/I] or [I]/wg reload[/I]
[/LIST]



